Question: Do you think we're obligated to help others?
Answer: We are not forced to help others no. But there is no issue of taking out the time out of your day to check up on your friends and family to make sure they are actually okay. Theres bit and issue to give a stranger a compliment to make their day better, because who knows what they are actually going through. Its not an issue to clean up your mess or help a worker in a restaurant clean up. Its not an issue to donate money to help a family or a cause out. Its not an issue to go out your way for someone in need who truly deserves it such as making blankets to give to the homeless. We never know what life someone is living or what's going on inside their minds. We tend to be rude and selfish to others or hold a grudge against them, say its not that bad get over it. But the truth is we never know the last moments we will have with those people... And some of you don't even realize the love or respect that person had for anyone until they are gone. ... The world is honestly a sad place. And we all need to come together to spread love and help each other out.

FOR the most wild, yet most homely narrative which I am about to pen, I neither expect nor solicit belief. Mad indeed would I be to expect it, in a case where my very senses reject their own evidence. Yet, mad am I not -- and very surely do I not dream. But to-morrow I die, and to-day I would unburthen my soul. My immediate purpose is to place before the world, plainly, succinctly, and without comment, a series of mere household events. In their consequences, these events have terrified -- have tortured -- have destroyed me. Yet I will not attempt to expound them. To me, they have presented little but Horror -- to many they will seem less terrible than barroques. Hereafter, perhaps, some intellect may be found which will reduce my phantasm to the common-place -- some intellect more calm, more logical, and far less excitable than my own, which will perceive, in the circumstances I detail with awe, nothing more than an ordinary succession of very natural causes and effects.
  
  From my infancy I was noted for the docility and humanity of my disposition. My tenderness of heart was even so conspicuous as to make me the jest of my companions. I was especially fond of animals, and was indulged by my parents with a great variety of pets. With these I spent most of my time, and never was so happy as when feeding and caressing them. This peculiarity of character grew with my growth, and, in my manhood, I derived from it one of my principal sources of pleasure. To those who have cherished an affection for a faithful and sagacious dog, I need hardly be at the trouble of explaining the nature or the intensity of the gratification thus derivable. There is something in the unselfish and self-sacrificing love of a brute, which goes directly to the heart of him who has had frequent occasion to test the paltry friendship and gossamer fidelity of mere Man.
  
  I married early, and was happy to find in my wife a disposition not uncongenial with my own. Observing my partiality for domestic pets, she lost no opportunity of procuring those of the most agreeable kind. We had birds, gold-fish, a fine dog, rabbits, a small monkey, and a cat.
  
  This latter was a remarkably large and beautiful animal, entirely black, and sagacious to an astonishing degree. In speaking of his intelligence, my wife, who at heart was not a little tinctured with superstition, made frequent allusion to the ancient popular notion, which regarded all black cats as witches in disguise. Not that she was ever serious upon this point -- and I mention the matter at all for no better reason than that it happens, just now, to be remembered.
  
  Pluto -- this was the cat's name -- was my favorite pet and playmate. I alone fed him, and he attended me wherever I went about the house. It was even with difficulty that I could prevent him from following me through the streets.

This week with Lauren - 5/5/19
  
  tbh this week was hard for me mentally, but I had a lot of good times too thanks to my good pals ❤️ if you are having a hard time for any reason today/this week, remember that all you have to do is try. Don’t expect yourself to be a superhuman right now and get everything done flawlessly bc that’s just not gonna happen. Do little things to take care of yourself. Go on a 20 minute walk in the morning to keep your body moving, actually wash your face and brush your teeth every night, go to bed before midnight, set a timer for 10 minutes and just pray. Make a goal for each day that’s something you can actually achieve. Don’t forget that people care about you too. Reach out to your family and friends let them know you’re going through a hard time right now and let them know if there’s anything they can do to help you, even if that just means listening or reminding you to do your laundry or clean your room or do your homework. Most importantly remember that everything happening right now is just temporary, things WILL change. They always do. And if you are putting in effort everyday to live the life you want to live, soon enough you will find yourself where you want to be ❤️

Question: Do you live alone? I'd like to know... how do you live when you're alone? I think It's a terrible thing to be lonesome .

I grew up in california sharing a room with my sisters Lisa and Danielle. We lived in a house with a total of 13 of us. ( my parents, 6 sisters/girls  6 brothers/boys). This lasted up until may of 2015, when we decided to move to Tennessee. The older girls : Christina, Katherine, Lisa and Amy all moved into an apartment with each other
  
  My parents, me, Dani, and our younger brothers christian, nick, and joey all lived in the family house
  
  And our older brothers Michael and Alex were still living in California but   had their own house as well
  
  Well as years went by :
  
  Christina got married to nick so she moved out - leaving a house to Kath,Lisa and Amy
  
  Dani turned 18 and moved out
  
  Michael- is a Realtor and travels alot
  
  Alex- travels and hardly is home
  
  So in the family house it leaves my parents, my younger brothers, and I and the dog. And our friends who come down from california to visit. We also have our own rooms as well

Answer:
Hey guys! You may have seen us on YouTube and wondered, who are these girls? We are 6 sisters from a family of 11 kids- yep, we also have 5 brothers! We started our band in our hometown in Northern California in 2007 and since then it's been quite the journey. From playing classic rock covers as a full band, to creating acapella arrangements of covers and uploading them to our YouTube channel, to moving to L.A. and signing with a major record label, to going the traditional "girl group" route, to completely rebelling from that and dressing super grungey and performing a 90 minute set of almost all acoustic songs, to leaving our record label and moving all the way to Nashville to become independent artists, we've come a long way since 2007! lol
  
  The ONE constant in our journey has always been YOU GUYS- our amazing, bizarre, international, devoted internet family, the Cim Fam!! We really could not have done any of this without you guys, and to say we are incredibly thankful and full of gratitude for each and every one of you is a HUGE understatement.. THANK YOU, from the bottom of our hearts! We love you guys so much, and every single decision we make is with you and your well-being in mind!
  
  Through this crazy and incredible journey, what we've learned is that the most important part of what we do is the MESSAGE. You guys poured out your hearts to us and shared your darkest secrets, and we realized the only thing we could do was pour our hearts out back to you and make music with the messages we believe will be helpful and positive to you. Our messages are anti-suicide, positive body image, strong self-worth, and finding Faith in the darkest of times. Our mission is to create music and art that reflects this strong core belief that NO ONE is a lost cause- there is hope for everyone, no matter how "far gone" they may seem.
  
  We have cried in front of you guys dozens of times on stages from the U.S. to South America to Europe to the Philippines. We have held you, hugged you and listened to your stories in person in meet and greet lines and backstage. We know your hearts, and we care deeply for you guys as if you were our own brothers and sisters, and that is what makes us family!

IOS or Android?

Pros/cons for each?
Answer:
IOS:
  
  Pros: Gets updates for a long time, social media apps are more compatible, Facetime, iMessage & blue bubbles, better battery if you get an iPhone 11, more fluency in ecosystem, better facial recognition software, nicer looking widgets
  
  Cons: Lots of bugs, costs more than it's worth, boring bc of lack of customization, still uses lightning port, gets new features really late
  
  Android:
  
  Pro: Very customizable - can customize almost anything, expandable storage, more apps, splitscreen & popup window option, Google Assistant (better than all the others), very fast charging, more durable, keyboard clipboard, more innovative, faster web browsing, better file transferring between computers, button remapping
  
  Con: Only 3yrs of updates, tends to get more lag than Apple phones, social media apps less compatible (less features within the apps)
  
  But the real pros and cons really depend on the phone....some phones that run Android are very wack bc many companies make budgets phones. So, with phones like Samsung, Pixel, Huawei and OnePlus, you get a lot more pros than you would with any other Android running phone. Those are the only ones that can really compete with Apple phones.
  
  For me, I have both, but I prefer my Android phone (Samsung) as my main driver

Question: Nevermind...
Who is the closest person to you? What made them closer than anyone else?
Answer:
It's actually a little hard to answer that bc I have a friend who I have grown up with -- we knew each other since we were practically babies, but nowadays, I know we don't tell each other a lot. We live across the street and her family used to always have dinner with mine and we have summer activities we do together so we were pretty close, but then as we became teenagers, we both became a bit more reserved with our separate lives I think. I knew there were bigs things in her life she wasn't telling me so I kinda stopped trusting her.
  
  I would consider her my closest friend, but at the same time, I have told some of my deeper secrets to other friends bc I felt like I could talk to them more. They told me their sh*t so I told them mine and that made us closer. If we lived nearer to each other, we might be really close by now. But since this first friend lives across the street, we are always being in each other's lives, so I may not be the closest with her, but she's the one I see the most, hang out with the most, known for longest....so basically, it's hard to answer that question.
